node.text: This summer, cool off with my “Chili-Lime Fruit Salad” packed with fresh watermelon, papaya, kiwi, pineapple, and blueberries! 🍉 Plus, I’m making a yummy “Burrata Caprese Salad” with beautiful heirloom tomatoes, fresh basil, garlic, and of course, lots of delicious Burrata! 😋 You’re gonna love these quick and easy recipes! 💕 Recipe link in IG stories!

node.text: I cooked up my delicious “Ginger-Miso Pasta Salad” with my friends over at @todayshow to show them how easy and refreshing this recipe is! 💕 With a few Persian cucumbers, bell peppers, edamame, broccoli, and toasted sesame seeds, you’re gonna love adding this summer salad to your menu because it packs easily and can be served at any temperature! ☀️ Recipe link in IG stories! 😘

node.text:
aren’t we tired of body shaming women yet?! smh.
I was going to delete my stories because it’s a little embarrassing and scary to be so vulnerable. But then I realized it was hitting a ‘good’ nerve with so many of you who were so sweet to dm and share your same vulnerability and struggles. We all could use a little more kindness and patience and grace, because we just never know what someone else is going through. 
 So here it is. Not deleting. Owning it. ♥️
#compassion

node.text:
🥶 It’s been chilly out, so let’s cook my yummy “Greek Lemon Chicken Soup” to warm you and the family up! 🥰 This recipe is so Deeelicious! 💫 
•
INGREDIENTS✨
Deselect All
4 cups chicken stock
1 small carrot, halved 
1 stalk celery, halved 
1 sprig dill, plus sprigs for garnish
1 shallot, halved
Kosher salt 
1 boneless, skinless chicken breast (about 6 ounces) 
1/3 rounded cup orzo 
2 large eggs 
3 tablespoons fresh lemon juice
________
DIRECTIONS✨
1. In a large saucepan, combine the chicken stock with 4 cups water, the carrot, celery, dill, shallot and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken breast, lower the heat to a bare simmer, and cook, turning occasionally, until just cooked through, 12 to 15 minutes. Transfer the breast to a plate. Remove the carrot, celery, dill and shallot from the broth, and discard.
•
2. Raise the heat to a brisk simmer. Add the orzo to the broth and simmer until tender, 6 to 8 minutes. Meanwhile, shred the chicken.
•
3. Whisk the eggs with the lemon juice in a medium bowl. When the orzo is cooked, slowly ladle about 1/2 cup of the hot broth into the egg mixture while whisking constantly. Pour back into the saucepan and cook, whisking occasionally, just until the broth returns to a simmer, about 2 minutes. Turn off the heat, add the shredded chicken, and season with salt.
•
4.Ladle the soup into bowls and garnish with dill.

node.text: 💕Good Morning from #kidsbakingchampionship 🧁😘 #BTS

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Valerie Bertinelli on August 22, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: 👩🏻‍🍳 I’m cookin’ up a little summer play on a Caprese Salad with my refreshing “Burrata with Grilled Peaches” recipe! 🍑 This dish is super easy to make. 💕 All you gotta do is grill some peaches with a bit of olive oil, salt, and pepper and toss them in a mix of mild Calabrian chili paste with olive oil and red wine vinegar for the dressing.  Next, grab about eight ounces of Burrata and place on your grilled peaches, then top those beauties with fresh mint and torn basil leaves! 😋This dish is deelicious! I’ll show you how easy it is in the #FoodNetworkKitchen app! Recipe link in bio! 😘

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Valerie Bertinelli on August 20, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, drink and indoor.

node.text: 👩🏻‍🍳 After receiving a letter from a visually impaired fan who needs help in the kitchen, I decided to reach out to Chef Christine Ha, who is blind, for a bit of help with recipes that use all the senses. 💕 The menu includes Easy Vegetable Bolognese with Spaghetti Squash, No-Fuss Fancy Garlic Bread, Blueberry Rosemary Bramble , and to satisfy our sweet tooth, a Strawberry Shortcake Ice Cream Cake! 🍰 Tune in this Sunday 1130 AM on @foodnetwork! 😘

node.text: 👩🏻‍🍳 With so many birthdays coming up, I invite my friend Debo over to give me some tips on gift-wrapping. 🥰 I’m making Summery Shrimp, Corn and Avocado Dip, Homemade Chili Lime Tortilla Chips, Smokey Caprese Sandwiches, Vanilla Coconut Rice Pudding with Homemade Vanilla Sugar and Kumquat-cello! (exhales hehe)  And Debo shows me how to make my edible gifts look amazing with fun and funky accents! 😍 It’s gonna be deelicious!! Tune-In @foodnertwork this Sunday 1130AM! 😘

node.text: 👩🏻‍🍳 It’s Taco Tuesday, so; I’m gonna show you how to make my “Wonton Taco Salad Cups!” 🌮 These cute little cups are packed with ground turkey meat, onions, fresh garlic, and dried oregano topped with a dollop of sour cream, salsa, a little shredded cheese, and diced avocado! 🥑 These bite-sized cups are a great after-school snack and a great starter when entertaining friends and family! 😋 Come and see how easy they are to make in the #FoodNetworkKitchen app! 😘 Link in bio!
